cloudflare-ddns(1) -- dynamically update a DNS record
=====================================================

## SYNOPSIS

`cloudflare-ddns` [<api_token> <record_name>] [--config <file>]

## DESCRIPTION

`cloudflare-ddns` is a tool that can be used to dynamically update a DNS record using Cloudflare's API.

This tool is a oneshot program: you run it, it updates the DNS record, and it terminates. To make it run periodically you could use a systemd timer or a cron job.

To run the tool you'll need an [API token](https://dash.cloudflare.com/profile/api-tokens); cloudflare-ddns only needs the Zone.DNS edit permission.

You can run `cloudflare-ddns` in two different ways: you can pass the API Token and the record name as command line arguments, or you can use a ini configuration file, located in `@sysconfdir@/cloudflare-ddns/config.ini`, by passing no arguments at all. If you prefer, you can even use a configuration file in a custom location, using `--config file-path`.

## OPTIONS

Command line options

  * `--config`:
    Custom path to the config file

## EXAMPLES

    $ cloudflare-ddns
    New IP: 149.20.4.15
